The paper deals with improving "learning to search" approaches to structured prediction, which is a problem commonly studied in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses algorithmic improvements, which is a topic relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper emphasizes the reduction in programming time, which is a concern in software engineering (cs.SE).
